<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I almost forgot to give out MY tactic! Im level 12.<p>

Boy see what happens when I get to babblen? Ive found this series of spells useful when dealing with  little gnome invaders. Maybe you can use it. &lt;shrugs&gt;<p>

First buff yourself up and have your pet. I keep mist, str on my pet and myself. As well I keep see inviso and lesser shielding on myself too. Cant tell you how many near death traps Ive side stepped due to just seeing a couple inviso enemies lurking around.<p>

Second find yourself a target, now get up close if you can so you can swing your melee weapon while ya cast. Attack! Cast mesmerize. Then Chaotic feedback or maybe dispell magic on them. Cast mesmerize again! If its a player and he starts to bag up his gear a shot of eye of confusion is in order now. Chaoitic feedback again now!<p>

You can mix in an enfeeblement spell as well, situation will tell ya whats best. Ive been exploring a bit with color flux, but havent made any decision on whether I like it or not. Ive heard people rave about it, but I just dont know.<p>

Before I learned the tactic I just told you I tried to root and dd my targets, which can work fine on weak creatures, but in player versus player it just doesnt cut it. Our DD spells are lacking is the best way to put it. And you cant just order your pet in while you hide behide a big tree...unlike some other classes. Your THINKING human target will dispell magic or gate on you, most mindless creatures who might try to waddle away with a bar of health.<p>

Well there, maybe it will help someone anyone. If not, maybe you can help me! LOL<p>

Roeth<br>
A elf enchanter<br>
Tallon server.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
