<td width="10"><img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/SmallNew.gif" border="0" alt="New Message"></td><td width="50%"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>RE:Tactics of an enchanter? (modified 0 times)</b> </font></td><td width="50%" align="RIGHT"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>aaeni</b></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I have a 31st lvl druid on Tallon Zek, and have recently changed over to an enchanter character. Why? PvP!! I've fought every class there is, and my worst assbeatings have been when an enchanter was around. They mana sieve you, they stun you, (preventing gate) they sic their pet on you, they mez you....they kill your magic resist, so that a root lasts FOREVER. Team up with a warrior, whirl your target while the warrior pounds it; the enemy cant cast, cant run, nothing. Only die.  The enemy has a pet? Mez it. I did this to a darkelf in blackburrow...he came back and stared at his pet, he had no idea why it was just sitting there. A paladin promptly slew him.<p>

Charm: outnumbered, waiting for guildmates to show up? charm a griffawn or something, send it at the enemy from extreme range. Keeps them injured and low on mana. Can be risky though, charm has a habit of breaking.<p>

I saw a high lvl wiz get tooled by an enchanter and druid...enchanter mana-sieved wiz out of mana. Wiz runs, enchanter meds with clarity. When it is time to use tracking to find wiz, enchanter has twice the mana. Or more.<p>

Color flux rocks...it is ALWAYS memmed. My bottom three slots are Tashan, color flux, Mez. Someone is trying to gate? get next to them and color flux...interrupt. If they have been tashaned, it should get thru.  Color flux also allows you to stun a mob and have time to cast Mez.<p>

One of the greatest things about an enchanter on a PvP server is not having to be dependent on equipment. Unless you try to be a wiz wannabe and root and nuke, you should always have enough mana if yer int is high. My druid is covered with expensive gear that is hard to get...i usually have to bag up. OTOH, you kill my enchanter, all you get is a crappy ring or some cloth armor. Whoopie. With a 127 int, i rarely go under half mana in a fight.<p>

Cheers,<br>
Aaeni<br>
Tallon Zek</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
