<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Well if you're lookin for great strategies to try out head on over to casters realm and take a look at their spells section.   Theres a bulletin board for each spell, and (although a lot of the advice has cost me exp) the advice there is great.<br>
Being an enchanter means you have to change strategies way too often, depending on level and charisma who you got in party etc.<br>
As for soloing, I just charmed a centaur foal and sent it after an archer.  while the two pounded each other, I debuffed the archer a bit and choked, and when my pet got a bit hurt, I cast chase the moon on the archer.  He ran off, finished getting killed, and then my pet came back with so low health that I was able to take him out with one dot.  A red archer and blue foal made great exp, easily covering the exp loss I took when I attempted to repeat :)<br>
when a charm breaks, just enthrall and mem blur it--you can kill it later if you want</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
