<tr>
<td width="10"><img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/SmallNew.gif" border="0" alt="New Message"></td><td width="50%"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>RE:Tactics of an enchanter? (modified 0 times)</b> </font></td><td width="50%" align="RIGHT"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>Ayla Rainbow</b></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">One of the reasons people are reluctant to share tactics is because of the designers at EverNerf.  Every time enchanters use their spells in an intelligent way and the word gets out, these abilities are weakened to the point of uselessness.  So, when enchanters find a tactic that works, they tend to keep it to themselves.  <p>

Case in point: Whirl til you Hurl<br>
This spell used to be the mainstay spell of enchanters.  It was a good longlasting spell that functioned similarly to the snare of other classes, except the MOB would stay in place.  This allowed Enchanters to attack the mob, get the pet involved, then Whirl, back away and Dot till it was dead.  Verant found out that Enchanters could actually *Oh NO!* solo, so they nerfed WTYH and the related Dyn's Dizzying Draught to their current useless state.  <p>

Good luck learning any real tactics from higher level Enchanters.  The successful Enchanter knows what happens every time we share our knowledge of workable tactics - we get nerfed.     <p>

This is, of course, not how it should work.  I helped found the Enchanted Circle, a guild for Enchanters only, just so we could share the good information of tactics, strategies and trade skills with our fellow enchanters.  <p>

But apparently, Verant is comprised of Shadow Men and Necros who do whatever they can to make our characters into simple Clarity and Alacrity buffers, utterly dependant on others for our experience.  In no other class has the ability to solo been so completely disabled as in the higher level enchanters.  <p>

One solution: Reprogram the whirl spells so they do just that: Whirl the mob.  If the mob could still attack you, but it was spinning, it should only hit you when it was facing in your direction.  This would be an easy effect to program for any competent programmer, and would fit in with the gameplay in an interesting and fun way.<p>

<br>
Ayla Rainbow<br>
Guild Administrator<br>
&lt;Enchanted Circle&gt;<br>
http://ecguild.cjb.net/</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
